- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with computational simulations of material deformation and recrystallization, which falls under the purview of computational engineering and science. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): This category is less likely, but the paper does mention the use of 3D experiments and full-field crystal plasticity simulations, which could involve multimedia visualization techniques. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper assesses the efficiency of parallel implementation of the developed methods, which could fall under distributed and parallel computing.
